The Rivers Government says it is excited hosting the 18th All African Senior Badminton Championships in Port Harcourt. Gov. Wilson Wike disclosed this at the opening ceremony of the Championships tagged Port Harcourt 2019 on Monday. Wike, represented by the Deputy Governor, Dr Ipalibo Harry-Banigo, thanked the Badminton Confederation of Africa (BCA) for granting Nigeria the hosting right. Wike noted that sports was an important aspect of human life as it drives unity and development.